(490, 1, '2020-03-19 10:25:12', '2020-03-19 10:25:12', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the blazing summer day, there was a cicada lazily lying around under healthy green foliage, holds on to its musical instrument and sings all day long. The cicada suddenly sees an ant that is struggling to carry a huge grain of rice and slowly passing by. Leisurely, the cicada said:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>â€œHey ant, on such a sunny day like this, why donâ€™t you take a break? Why must you exhaust yourself like that.â€&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Heard what the cicada said, the ant raised his head slightly, as he wiped away the sweat he responds. â€œOh Cicada? Of course I want to take a break, but winter will come. If I don\'t worry about food storage now, I don\'t know how my kids will live in the winter. â€&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>â€œHa ha, oh dear ant, your worries are still too far away. There are still summer and autumn and after that it will be winter. Why donâ€™t you take a rest, come here, Iâ€™ll sing you a song.â€</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The ant replied: â€œThanks cicada, but Iâ€™m busy working, maybe Iâ€™ll listen when I have free time. Itâ€™s late so Iâ€™ll be moving on now!â€</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seeing that the cicada pursed his lips, slowly shook it head and said to himself: \"What a pitiful ant, canâ€™t even enjoy summer, why live life so miserable like that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, the cicada once a again carried on singing, embraced the warmth of the summer sun. Time keeps passing by, autumn left and winter arrived, the colorful sunlight was no more, thereâ€™s only white snow and cold wind. Slowly trudging through the barren ground, the cicada is now trembling due to the cold and starvation.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->